Capability.TR_description: Comma delimited list of supported ATM modes: - GlobalFairness - WeightedFairness or - None Returns None if ATM is not supported by the platform. Additional algorithms may be added in the future.

Enable.TR_description: Enables or disables the ATM feature.

Mode.TR_description: The current ATM mode. Enumeration of one of the supported modes listed by Capability , or None if no modes are supported.

SSIDWeights.TR_description: Comma separated list of weights for SSIDs on this band, for example 70,15,10,5,0,0,0,0

Capability.TR_description: Comma delimited list of supported bandsteering modes. Enumeration of: - BalanceStations - FastStaTo5G - DualBandStaTo5G - BalanceChannelLoad - RSSI - RSSIThresholdAndChannelLoad - RSSIThresholdAndMaxBssSta - RSSIThresholdAdvanced or - None Returns None if bandsteering is not supported by the platform. Additional algorithms may be added in the future.

Mode.TR_description: The current ATM mode. Enumeration of one of the supported modes listed by 'Capability', or None if no modes are supported.

SSIDNumberOfEntries.TR_description: The number of entries in the 'SSID' table

Active.TR_description: True if bandsteering is active. Bandsteering may be enabled via the 'Enable' parameter but remain inactive (this parameter is false) in any of the following conditions: - One of the radios is disabled or inactive - The SSID is disabled or inactive on one or both bands - The SSID names do not match across bands - The SSID security settings do not match across bands - All required parameters must be configured

Blacklist24GNumberOfEntries.TR_description: The number of entries in the 'Blacklist24G' table

BlacklistTimeout.TR_description: Value in milliseconds that defines the time before an entry in the 2.4GHzTempBlackListTable expires.

Capable5GNumberOfEntries.TR_description: The number of entries in the 'Capable5G' table

ClearBlacklist24G.TR_description: Setting to true clears the 2.4 GHz Blacklist table. Returns false when read.

ClearCapable5G.TR_description: Setting to true clears the 5 GHz Capable table. Returns false when read.

DeltaThreshold.TR_description: This delta (in dBm) will be used when comparing the RSSI of the probe request on 5 GHz of an associated client. It can lower the threshold by this value.

Enable.TR_description: Enables or disables Bandsteering for this SSID. this parameter can only be set to true if '#.Mode' is set to something other than None .

RSSIThreshold.TR_description: In case of a 5 GHz capable device that sends out a direct probe request on 5 GHz or a broadcast probe request on 5 GHz when associated already, this threshold will define if the device will be added or removed from the 2.4GHzTempBlackListTable (i.e. when the RSSI is lower / worse than this threshold or when the RSSI is higher than the threshold). - Units: dBm

EntryTime.TR_description: Time when the client was added to this table.

TimeRemaining.TR_description: Time remaining before the client is removed from this table.

EntryTime.TR_description: Time when the client was added to this table.

AllowTime.TR_description: The time in milliseconds that the client is allowed to connect to an SSID in the BlacklistSelector list before it gets softblocked again. This timer is also reset when connecting to the PrivateSSIDSelector SSID.

ClearClientBlacklist.TR_description: Setting to true clears the ClientBlacklist table. Returns false when read.

ClientBlacklistNumberOfEntries.TR_description: The number of entries in the 'ClientBlacklist' table

Enable.TR_description: Enables or disables the Softblocking feature.

PrivateSSIDSelector.TR_description: SSID number for the Private SSID (1, 2, ... N). For example, if the first SSID on each band is the Private SSID, this value should be set to 1 .

PublicSSIDSelector.TR_description: Comma delimited list of Public SSID numbers to block when a client is present in the ClientBlacklist table. For example, if the Public SSIDs are the 3rd and 5th SSID on each band, this value would be 3,5 .

StatusCodeOnAuthResp.TR_description: The value of the status code in the Authentication Response sent to the client who was softblocked on authentication request. Setting this to 0 means NOT sending Authentication Responses.

TypeIgnoreProbeReq.TR_description: Defines how the Probe Requests are responded to when a softblock event is triggered. These cases can be 0, 1 or 2. Value Range: - 0 (Ignore probe responses of all devices) - 1 (Ignore probe responses of blacklist-devices) - 2 (Send probe responses)

WaitingTime.TR_description: The waiting time in milliseconds that the gateway will not respond to any Probe or Association Request done by a client on an SSID in the PublicSSIDSelector list whose MAC address is present in the ClientBlacklist table.

LastAssocTime.TR_description: Time when the client last associated.
